  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Sustainable Livelihood Promotion for Tsunami Victims in Cuddalore</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project will assist a total of 800 families in the Tsunami-affected area in South India. The immediate relief support has resettled the families, but they still lack opportunities to build sustainable livelihoods. The 400 original project families will receive 800 goats, 20 bucks, 4,000 chicks (20 chicks each for 200 families), fodder seed/saplings and vegetable seed. Project participants will receive trainings on Heifer Cornerstones, self-help group management, improved animal management, gender, kitchen gardening and fodder production.  Veterinary services and support will also be provided. This project will also provide refresher trainings to the self-help group members of phase I Tsunami project in Cuddalore district.</narrative>
  </description>
